<taxonomicName box="[927,1066,1746,1772]" class="Fusulinata" family="Aljutovellidae" genus="Skelnevatella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="19" pageNumber="544" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1066,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="544">Skelnevatella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The transfer of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Putrya &amp; Leontovich" authorityYear="1948" box="[1253,1407,1746,1772]" class="Fusulinata" family="Profusulinellidae" genus="Profusulinella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="19" pageNumber="544" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="skelnevatica">
<emphasis box="[1253,1407,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="544">P. skelnevatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rauzer-Chernousova" authorityYear="1938" box="[813,948,1778,1804]" class="Fusulinata" family="Profusulinellidae" genus="Profusulinella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="19" pageNumber="544" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="priscoidea">
<emphasis box="[813,948,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="544">P. priscoidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species to the new genus (
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1403,1778,1804]" class="Fusulinata" family="Aljutovellidae" genus="Skelnevatella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="19" pageNumber="544" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1262,1403,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="544">Skelnevatella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[813,932,1810,1836]" class="Fusulinata" family="Aljutovellidae" genus="Priscoidella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="19" pageNumber="544" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,932,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="544">Priscoidella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) proposed by Solovieva (in Rauzer-Chernousova 
<emphasis box="[813,867,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="544">et al.</emphasis>
1996) is doubtful.
</paragraph>
